1
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:34,093
It was a day like no other.

2
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:35,197
It was a day like no other.

3
00:00:38,497 --> 00:00:42,035
It was a day
I had always dreamed of...

4
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:44,241
a day I would never forget.

5
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:50,457
Will you marry this woman
and take her to your heart..

6
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:53,339
Forever devoted and forever young?

7
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:55,339
I will.

8
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:59,799
And will you marry this man
and take him to your heart...

9
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,351
forever devoted and forever young?

10
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:04,348
I will.

11
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:07,147
Would you now place
the ring on her finger?

12
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:12,978
I now declare you-

13
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,988
What a shame we had uninvited guests.

14
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:24,745
Eh! I'll have
what I came for this day!

15
00:01:27,129 --> 00:01:29,120
Jack politely asked them to leave.

16
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:31,330
Kiss steel, bastard!

17
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:45,435
Jack!

18
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:55,025
Aha!

19
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,482
Get her!

20
00:02:01,163 --> 00:02:03,200
Jack!

21
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:05,748
Hold tight! I'm coming!

22
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:12,504
His temper flared, but
he fought like a gentleman.

23
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:17,835
Jack! Jack!

24
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:23,090
Whoa!

25
00:02:32,444 --> 00:02:35,527
Oh! Uh!

26
00:02:35,614 --> 00:02:38,231
My one, true love had fought bravely...

27
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:40,316
but it wasn't enough.

28
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:54,292
There was only room for one more.

29
00:02:54,383 --> 00:02:56,715
It was either my love or myself.

30
00:02:56,802 --> 00:03:01,421
- You take it, my love.
- Never. Those maggots will not have you.

31
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,426
They will not have me for long.

32
00:03:03,517 --> 00:03:05,474
I have consumption...

33
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,471
and will be dead
before the year is out.

34
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,803
You were gonna marry me
with consumption?

35
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:11,935
Why didn't you tell me?

36
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:14,016
I didn't want to spoil things.

37
00:03:14,111 --> 00:03:16,022
- Go!
- No!

38
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:18,104
Live to fight another day!

39
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:23,984
Whatever makes you happy.

40
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:32,710
With Jack, my happiness always came first.

41
00:03:34,423 --> 00:03:36,460
I faced my fate alone.

42
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:39,713
The 10 turned to 20,
the 20 to 40.

43
00:03:39,803 --> 00:03:43,137
Could this be the end of my freedom,
my salvation, my-

44
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,760
Hey! Gorgeous!

45
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:49,594
Hey! Hiya, Joanie!

46
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:58,860
♪♪

47
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:00,904
Wow!

48
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:03,899
What happened?

49
00:04:07,122 --> 00:04:09,614
♪♪

50
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:40,566
“Was this the end of my freedom,
my salvation?”

51
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:45,399
My career?

52
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:48,156
♪♪

53
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:11,008
Heads up!

54
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:13,013
Oh!

55
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:38,164
♪♪

56
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:49,676
♪♪

57
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:57,263
Whoo! Ah!

58
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:59,769
Gorgeous day.
Huh, gorgeous?

59
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:03,979
We got blue skies,
nice, warm water...

60
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:06,734
and a cold beer.

61
00:06:06,825 --> 00:06:10,409
Honey, did you get any more Buds?

62
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:13,487
No. I just didn't have time today...

63
00:06:13,582 --> 00:06:15,664
to ravage the Riviera
for your beer.

64
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,411
Tough day, huh?

65
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:19,960
Yeah, you could say
it was tough.

66
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:23,710
But then, when the going gets tough,
the tough-

67
00:06:25,844 --> 00:06:27,801
I don't know what the tough do.

68
00:06:27,888 --> 00:06:29,879
I don't know what the pirates do.

69
00:06:29,973 --> 00:06:31,964
I don't know
what anybody does. Jack-

70
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,800
Oh, honey, I know.
I know, baby. I know.

71
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:37,933
Hey, I know.

72
00:06:38,023 --> 00:06:41,812
But look out there.
What do you see?

73
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:45,065
- Bloomingdale's?
- No. Greece.

74
00:06:45,155 --> 00:06:45,922
Greece?

75
00:06:45,946 --> 00:06:48,318
Yeah. Mykonos, Lesbos,
Crete, ouzo, olive oil.

76
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:50,365
- Honey, we're going!
- Wait a minute.

77
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:53,444
You said we were gonna
go back to New York for a while.

78
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:56,405
Absolutely.
When the summer's over, we're goin'.

79
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:59,332
Aw, Jack! We've been on this boat
half a year now.

80
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,626
I need shore leave.
I promised Gloria...

81
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:03,670
I would finish that book
three months ago.

82
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:05,839
And I can't.
I don't know what happens next.

83
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:09,169
- - I thought you said you
wanted to sail around the world with me.

84
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:12,755
Well, I do, but-
but not all of it this week.

85
00:07:12,849 --> 00:07:15,386
I mean, Jack,
this is just becoming a blur.

86
00:07:15,477 --> 00:07:18,720
I mean,
exotic ports and great parties...

87
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,975
and spectacular sunsets.

88
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:24,855
- It's not enough.
- It's not enough?

89
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:27,312
You sound like somebody
who's got what they wanted...

90
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:30,147
and now they don't want
what they got.

91
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:32,778
- I want to do something serious.
- Serious? Oh, come on.

92
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:35,531
Aw, Jack. How much romance
can one woman take?

93
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:37,909
Joan Wilder?

94
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:44,002
- From your most devoted fan.
- Thank you.

95
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:54,880
“This afternoon we shall meet.
Awaiting the moment.”

96
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:56,155
What's this afternoon?

97
00:07:56,179 --> 00:07:58,889
Well, it must be somebody
coming to the reception.

98
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:02,768
That's not till next Tuesday.

99
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:04,973
This is next Tuesday, Jack.

100
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,289
Just-Okay.

101
00:08:21,376 --> 00:08:23,583
I thought you said
you were gonna get a car.

102
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:26,583
If I knew it was Tuesday,
it would've been here. I'm sorry.

103
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:28,584
Oh. That's all right.

104
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:32,088
What do you say we spin that roulette wheel
a few times while we're down there?

105
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,169
Sounds great.

106
00:08:40,562 --> 00:08:43,600
Merci, monsieur. Au revoir.

107
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:45,601
- Merci. Bye.
- Jack. Jack?

108
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:47,603
- Yeah?
- She can't leave now.

109
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:49,651
- Why not?
- What do you mean, why not?

110
00:08:49,738 --> 00:08:51,799
- Don't be ridiculous. Joan. Joan, darling.
- Oh, my God.

111
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:54,781
I am your biggest fan!
I have read all your books.

112
00:08:54,868 --> 00:08:57,906
Well, thank you very much.

113
00:08:57,996 --> 00:09:00,454
I'm so happy to see you!

114
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:03,828
- This is my publisher, Gloria Horne.
- Oh, your publisher.

115
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:07,912
- And-And this is-
- Oh, you are Mr. Wilder?

116
00:09:08,006 --> 00:09:12,500
- No. I'm Mr. Colton. Jack Colton.
- What do you do, Mr. Colton?

117
00:09:12,594 --> 00:09:15,712
- Casino work.
- Casino work?

118
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:18,046
Yeah. I think I'll go downstairs
and punch in. Excuse me.

119
00:09:18,141 --> 00:09:20,974
- Excuse me one second.
- But, Jack?

120
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:23,428
I'll be back.

121
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,603
I've got to have a drink.

122
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:28,978
Literary functions
are not exactly Jack's speed.

123
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:32,858
The guy's favorite author is the man
who wrote “Pull tab to open.”

124
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:34,397
I am his favorite author.

125
00:09:34,421 --> 00:09:36,986
You're telling me it's
none of my business?

126
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:41,321
Let me tell you something. Jack is not
the marrying kind. I am worried about you.

127
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:44,031
You're the girl who never gets a book
back late to the library.

128
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:46,207
You are three months
past your deadline.

129
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:48,501
Now, what gives with you?
Un scotch double.

130
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:51,125
My heart just isn't in it.

131
00:09:51,216 --> 00:09:54,504
I mean-Romance just doesn't
seem real to me anymore.

132
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,710
Real? You don't write “real.”

133
00:09:56,805 --> 00:09:59,116
You write about people
that sail off into the goddamn sunset.

134
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,507
What about the next day
when the sun comes up?

135
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:04,184
There is no next day.
That's why it's a romance.

136
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:07,262
You've got to stop confusing real life
with a romantic novel.

137
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,348
Joanie, just finish it.

138
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:12,355
I can't. I mean, after 17 books...

139
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,402
I don't know
how it ends anymore.

140
00:10:14,489 --> 00:10:16,446
Then permit me to tell you.

141
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:22,824
It doesn't end.

142
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:26,782
It only begins anew
when you journey down the Nile with me.

143
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:30,998
- Have you got the right woman?
- No.

144
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,046
My name is Omar Khalif a...

145
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:36,717
and I've traveled 1,000 miles
to tell you I need you.

146
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:40,216
- You sent me the flowers.
- They pale by your beauty.

147
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:42,217
Oh, marry him.

148
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:46,393
- I read about you.
- Yes, I know. Time magazine.

149
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:51,064
I'm afraid the Western press
cannot understand the spirit of my vision.

150
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:54,769
You are a writer.
You can understand.

151
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:57,981
So, Joan Wilder,
you must come and write my story.

152
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:01,358
I only write romance novels.

153
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:05,070
Yes, and you haven't finished
the one you're working on right now.

154
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,873
You are a gifted storyteller.

155
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,247
You create heroes
in a world of cynics.

156
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:13,328
Journey down the Nile with me...

157
00:11:13,423 --> 00:11:15,585
and I'll give you a chance
to record history.

158
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:18,007
- Come. We must leave today.
- Joanie!

159
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:21,303
In just four nights,
I will become emperor...

160
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:23,426
and you will have
the exclusive story.

161
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,427
They have emperors on the Nile?

162
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,429
They do now.

163
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,557
Oh, shit.

164
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:32,397
♪♪

165
00:11:48,917 --> 00:11:50,828
So, now what are we celebrating?

166
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:54,037
- The Nile.
- Oh, the Nile.

167
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:56,212
We've been invited to Africa.

168
00:11:56,299 --> 00:11:59,792
Uh, Jack Colton, Omar Khalif a.

169
00:11:59,886 --> 00:12:02,253
How do you do?

170
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:06,341
He's, uh, asked me-me-
to write his story.

171
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,425
It's just what
I've always wanted to do.

172
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:12,979
And now Joan's work will receive
the serious attention that it deserves.

173
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:17,310
And this will be her
biggest accomplishment-my biography.

174
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:22,443
What's so important down there
that you have to write the book now?

175
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:25,525
- Mr. Khalif a has-
- “Omar.” Please.

176
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:29,739
Omar has been chosen
to unite the tribes of the Nile...

177
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:32,699
and to end the internal strife
that has bloodied his land.

178
00:12:32,794 --> 00:12:36,162
He will carry on the work
of the Great Redeemer, who has disappeared.

179
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,419
- You have listened very well.
- You got all that in 20 minutes?

180
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:46,047
As a friend of Miss Wilder's,
you are very welcome to be my guest also.

181
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,507
- Thank you.
- My pleasure.

182
00:12:50,937 --> 00:12:53,520
Could I talk to you
for a minute, please?

183
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:01,190
I thought you wanted
to go to New York.

184
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:03,693
- That's all changed.
- That fast, huh?

185
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:05,899
But, Jack, to write a biography-

186
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:09,157
I mean, something important, something
real-This is what I've been looking for.

187
00:13:09,247 --> 00:13:12,285
You don't think this is a little bit
over your head, Joan?

188
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:14,992
I think it's a great chance.

189
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:17,077
You got your heart
set on it, huh?

190
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:24,342
Mine's set on Greece.

191
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:30,799
So, when are you gonna leave?

192
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:35,354
Tonight. Um,
he has a private jet, and-

193
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,522
Oh, he's got a private jet.

194
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:41,226
Well, what the hell.
We had a good run, didn't we?

195
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:45,861
Oh, Jack, come on. This is just
five or four weeks of research.

196
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:48,612
Maybe you're right.
Maybe we need a break.

197
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:50,770
Yeah, it's-it's been
kind of tough lately.

198
00:13:50,794 --> 00:13:51,491
Yeah.

199
00:13:51,581 --> 00:13:55,540
When the going gets tough,
the, uh, tough go to Greece.

200
00:13:58,004 --> 00:14:00,086
Well, I'll write you.

201
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:02,039
Where?

202
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:06,301
Yeah. Where?

203
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:22,901
I think I'll go down and give
that roulette wheel one more chance.

204
00:14:34,165 --> 00:14:36,497
You take care of yourself.

205
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:41,165
And you stay out of trouble.

206
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,635
Look out for her, will you?

207
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:57,094
I can offer you this comfort-
She leaves you for a higher purpose.

208
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:03,191
Yeah.

209
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:21,371
Free Al-Jawhara!

210
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:51,482
Don't be frightened.

211
00:15:51,576 --> 00:15:54,409
You know, a man of vision
has many enemies...

212
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,907
and my destiny
is to outsmart them.

213
00:15:56,998 --> 00:15:59,365
You see?

214
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:01,951
Like it?

215
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:04,285
It's okay.

216
00:16:46,589 --> 00:16:49,798
Well, sweetheart,
I guess it's just you and me.

217
00:16:49,884 --> 00:16:53,002
Goddamn it.
She was the best time I ever had.

218
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:55,962
Don't cry, scumbag.
I'll keep ya company.

219
00:16:57,934 --> 00:17:00,972
Cartagena, Colombia!

220
00:17:01,062 --> 00:17:02,973
- Long time, no-Oh, shit!
- Go ahead!

221
00:17:03,064 --> 00:17:05,806
Go ahead! Give me a reason.
Make my year.

222
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,751
Go easy with the gun.
All right, buddy? Easy.

223
00:17:07,775 --> 00:17:08,517
Did you miss me?

224
00:17:08,611 --> 00:17:11,603
I missed you.
You're all I thought about for six months.

225
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:13,779
They threw me in a jail-

226
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:16,608
filled with rejects
from the communicable disease ward.

227
00:17:16,702 --> 00:17:18,613
Every wacko, drippy...

228
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,696
open-sored lowlife
was in that joint-

229
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:24,203
all of them wantin' to hire on
as my proctologist.

230
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:27,706
And rats! Rats!
I'm full of rat bites.

231
00:17:27,797 --> 00:17:30,630
Ten weeks of rabies shots this long.

232
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,923
And all I thought of was you, Colton!

233
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:35,172
- Just you!
- I'm-I'm flattered, pal.

234
00:17:35,263 --> 00:17:38,130
And I'm-I'm sorry you had
such a tough time.

235
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:40,807
Uh, how about a hundred bucks?

236
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:43,885
Hundred bucks? I'll give you
a one-way ticket to harp land.

237
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:47,063
- No more jokes! What'd you do with it?
- What are you talking about?

238
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,265
The stone, moron!
I'm cocked here.

239
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,897
Listen, listen! Let's talk about this
like gentlemen, all right?

240
00:17:51,988 --> 00:17:54,195
Gentlemen? Did I tell ya
I got malaria in the jail?

241
00:17:54,282 --> 00:17:56,273
Every time I shake-
I shake like this.

242
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:58,699
You know what happens
if I shake my trigger finger?

243
00:17:58,786 --> 00:18:00,868
And I feel an attack
comin' on right now.

244
00:18:00,955 --> 00:18:03,617
You know what happens
if that happens?

245
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,353
You know what'll happen? It's the
end of Mr. Lucky. That's the end of-

246
00:18:06,377 --> 00:18:08,664
Holy shit!

247
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,665
- Holy shit!
- Quiet!

248
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:12,997
Next time,
you'll not be so lucky.

249
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:17,131
- I am Tarak. You must come with me now.
- What the hell are you?

250
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:20,464
- Omar steal our jewel-Al-Jawhara.
- Jewel?

251
00:18:20,558 --> 00:18:22,469
You were invited with the woman.

252
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:25,473
You can get into Omar's palace.
My people cannot.

253
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:28,555
What people? What the hell you
talkin' about? I don't know who you are.

254
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:31,232
- You must come to help me find the jewel!
- What jewel?

255
00:18:31,319 --> 00:18:34,139
The Jewel of the Nile-our
most priceless jewel.

256
00:18:34,163 --> 00:18:35,187
Oh, that jewel.

257
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:39,275
Omar has stolen my people's jewel,
Omar is a very bad man.

258
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,450
That scum!
I spit on him. Ptoo!

259
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:44,905
Jack, buddy. Let's help this nice man
get his jewel back.

260
00:18:44,999 --> 00:18:45,848
Yes, yes.

261
00:18:45,872 --> 00:18:48,492
I don't know where you're
from or what you're on...

262
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:51,294
but I'm sailing my boat tonight.

263
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:55,499
No! You must come to help find the
jewel now-before Omar kill many people.

264
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:59,587
As long as Omar have the jewel,
nothing can stop him.

265
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,887
Look, I'm going on the boat.

266
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,931
You guys can do what you want.

267
00:19:08,439 --> 00:19:11,147
The boat blew up.

268
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:15,393
My boat blew up.

269
00:19:15,488 --> 00:19:17,570
The boat blew up!

270
00:19:17,657 --> 00:19:19,694
Everything's gone.

271
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:25,408
Who are you-the Prince of Darkness?
Don't you got any friends?

272
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:27,705
This is the work of Omar.

273
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,037
Omar blew up my boat, huh?

274
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:34,211
Your woman is in danger too.
I will take you to him.

275
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:37,632
- I'm coming too!
- The hell you are!

276
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:41,086
Look, you owe me, Colton.

277
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:44,798
So wherever you're goin',
I'm goin'.

278
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:49,227
- Where we goin'?
- Africa.

279
00:20:19,719 --> 00:20:21,676
Do you recognize my home?

280
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:25,721
- I wrote this!
- Yes, in The Return of the King.

281
00:20:25,808 --> 00:20:30,143
I had the same uniforms designed.

282
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:36,057
♪♪

283
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:41,566
Hello.

284
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:43,568
Hi.

285
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:49,829
- Is all this yours?
- It belongs to the country, to my people.

286
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:52,407
Oh.

287
00:20:53,878 --> 00:20:56,791
Oh!

288
00:20:56,881 --> 00:20:59,043
Why point out the negative?

289
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:02,125
In three nights, in the city of Kadir,
the moon will be full...

290
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:05,257
and all my people
will unite behind me in peace.

291
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:07,805
And none of this will be necessary.

292
00:21:07,892 --> 00:21:12,136
- Now let me show you my humble house.
- Thank you.

293
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:15,517
Omar! Omar!

294
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:20,860
I'm really blessed.
My people love me.

295
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:24,530
It's, like-
Yes, they seem very en-enthusiastic.

296
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:32,785
Oh. This is a good shot for you-

297
00:21:32,875 --> 00:21:35,742
the little boy
holding up my picture.

298
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:38,624
Oh, yeah. That's wonderful.

299
00:21:58,901 --> 00:22:01,734
My humble house.

300
00:22:01,821 --> 00:22:04,688
You must forgive us.
We are a poor people.

301
00:22:13,624 --> 00:22:16,742
Everything you need,
they will bring to you.

302
00:22:16,836 --> 00:22:17,748
Oh, thank you.

303
00:22:17,772 --> 00:22:20,579
In my country, only
strangers say thank you.

304
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:22,664
Family and friends have no need.

305
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:27,752
- What was that?
- Cats.

306
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:30,680
- Come.
- Oh.

307
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:32,677
I have a cat.

308
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:43,897
- I hope this is satisfactory.
- Oh.

309
00:22:43,988 --> 00:22:47,276
Oh, yes. This is okay.
Uh, fine.

310
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:49,949
Here you will write
your masterpiece.

311
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:52,242
Ah. I have a few questions.

312
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:54,320
I see the writer is already at work.

313
00:22:54,415 --> 00:22:56,782
Good.

314
00:22:56,876 --> 00:22:59,288
Explore your new world.

315
00:22:59,378 --> 00:23:02,712
Feel free to go anywhere
and see anything...

316
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:05,665
talk to anyone.

317
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:09,093
I am glad you're here, Joan.
Together, we'll make history.

318
00:24:07,071 --> 00:24:09,153
It's like a fishbowl!

319
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:12,322
Why do these third world cesspools
always gotta be so hot?

320
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:16,027
Will you tell me that?

321
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:18,078
Hey. Where the hell you goin'?

322
00:24:23,045 --> 00:24:24,956
Holy shit!

323
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:38,175
♪♪

324
00:24:42,815 --> 00:24:47,560
Well, Colton, looks like
we've hitched our wagon to a star.

325
00:24:47,653 --> 00:24:51,021
♪♪

326
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:53,989
♪♪

327
00:24:56,120 --> 00:25:00,865
♪♪

328
00:25:16,390 --> 00:25:19,223
Stop that! Stop it!

329
00:25:27,026 --> 00:25:29,188
Excuse me.

330
00:25:29,278 --> 00:25:31,815
Um, what does this mean?

331
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:35,023
- Al-Jawhara.
- Al-Jawhara?

332
00:25:36,744 --> 00:25:40,078
- Do you speak English?
- “Give back the jewel.”

333
00:25:40,164 --> 00:25:41,950
Give back the jewel?

334
00:25:42,041 --> 00:25:44,032
Yeah.

335
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:52,215
Hey! You can't do that! I'm a professional!

336
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:02,224
We'll see about that.

337
00:26:04,521 --> 00:26:07,730
If you don't tell me
what the hell is going on here...

338
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:10,478
I am going to be on the first plane
back to New York.

339
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:12,526
It's impossible.

340
00:26:12,613 --> 00:26:15,401
Tomorrow we journey to Kadir.
You must be there.

341
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:17,482
It will be
your most important chapter.

342
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:20,193
I can't write this book
if you keep secrets from me.

343
00:26:20,287 --> 00:26:22,949
- What secrets?
- Al-Jawhara?

344
00:26:24,541 --> 00:26:26,532
What is the jewel?

345
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:31,370
The jewel is a legend.

346
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:34,082
I am real.

347
00:26:34,176 --> 00:26:37,510
Do not be distracted
from your mission, Joan Wilder.

348
00:26:37,596 --> 00:26:40,839
Make yourself comfortable.

349
00:26:40,933 --> 00:26:43,220
You'll stay with me
until our book is done.

350
00:26:44,228 --> 00:26:46,219
You can't keep me here.

351
00:26:48,774 --> 00:26:51,106
Go. You are free to leave.

352
00:26:54,113 --> 00:26:57,947
Only the worst kind of fool
would attempt our desert alone.

353
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:02,743
♪♪

354
00:27:06,792 --> 00:27:10,251
I gotta get off this camel.

355
00:27:10,337 --> 00:27:12,248
He's breakin' my ass.

356
00:27:12,339 --> 00:27:15,502
Colton. I can't take it.
I can't. No! No!

357
00:27:15,592 --> 00:27:17,299
Not the left one!
Oh, shit!

358
00:27:17,386 --> 00:27:19,593
Camp's comin' up. The left one!

359
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:24,015
♪♪

360
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:31,147
♪♪

361
00:27:33,235 --> 00:27:36,227
Come! You are welcome!

362
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:40,652
We have food!
We have drink!

363
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:42,779
You got a toilet?

364
00:27:42,870 --> 00:27:45,487
♪♪

365
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:49,949
So, how big is this jewel?

366
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:58,792
Very, very big. Very big. Very, very big.

367
00:27:58,886 --> 00:28:01,127
Very big. Very big.

368
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:03,883
Is it as big as this orange?

369
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:12,687
It's as big as an orange.

370
00:28:12,774 --> 00:28:15,516
The jewel is the heart
of our people.

371
00:28:15,611 --> 00:28:18,603
Omar steals
the heart of our people.

372
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:20,483
- Omar is thief!
- Omar is very bad man.

373
00:28:20,574 --> 00:28:23,817
Before Omar steal our jewel,
everything good.

374
00:28:23,911 --> 00:28:25,822
Now everything is shit!

375
00:28:25,913 --> 00:28:29,031
Omar is thief!

376
00:28:34,087 --> 00:28:36,249
You help us find the jewel...

377
00:28:36,340 --> 00:28:39,128
and we give you great reward.

378
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:41,710
But if you lie to us, you die!

379
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:46,346
But now we dance!

380
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:49,926
Yallah! Yallah! Yallah!

381
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,483
Whoa!

382
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:04,906
♪♪

383
00:29:21,051 --> 00:29:23,509
Look at these guys, Colton.

384
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:25,552
No sheep is safe tonight.

385
00:29:25,639 --> 00:29:29,928
♪♪

386
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:39,145
We split it
right down the middle, Colton.

387
00:29:39,236 --> 00:29:41,978
- Fifty-fifty.
- What are you talking about?

388
00:29:42,072 --> 00:29:45,690
Don't play stupid with me, partner.

389
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:47,695
The jewel!

390
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:50,653
And don't you even think
of messin' with me.

391
00:29:56,086 --> 00:30:00,125
Oh! What's that I hear-
a heart breakin'? You sap!

392
00:30:00,215 --> 00:30:02,206
Better keep your mind
on business, Romeo.

393
00:30:02,301 --> 00:30:05,510
You'll wind up getting yourself killed
over some broad who dumped you.

394
00:30:08,015 --> 00:30:10,222
Jewels! Ha!

395
00:30:10,309 --> 00:30:12,300
Oh, Omar. Ooh!

396
00:30:41,173 --> 00:30:43,915
I want you lot to be careful!

397
00:30:44,009 --> 00:30:46,797
Careful. See that word “Fragile”
on the side?

398
00:30:46,887 --> 00:30:49,845
It means don't drop-
What did I just say?

399
00:30:49,931 --> 00:30:52,764
I might love your country.
I might love your culture.

400
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:54,871
I might even love your people.
That means I love you.

401
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:57,762
But you drop another one of those boxes,
I'll smash your bloody face in!

402
00:31:00,609 --> 00:31:02,976
You tell Omar, right-Omar-

403
00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:06,108
that his special-effects wizard
has arrived.

404
00:31:06,198 --> 00:31:08,109
Come on then.

405
00:32:32,868 --> 00:32:35,280
War plans.

406
00:32:35,370 --> 00:32:37,281
Oh, my God.
What is he up to?

407
00:32:42,586 --> 00:32:45,624
Wait till Time magazine sees this.

408
00:33:10,113 --> 00:33:12,650
You bastard!
You burnt my hand!

409
00:33:12,741 --> 00:33:15,699
I didn't say it wouldn't burn.
I said it wouldn't hurt!

410
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:19,403
Look, there's no blistering. No blistering.
I've done it hundreds of times on stage.

411
00:33:19,498 --> 00:33:22,240
Look, this is not
a cheap theatrical stunt.

412
00:33:22,334 --> 00:33:25,076
It's a miracle.
My people have to believe it!

413
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:27,502
Omar, trust me.
Trust what I've got to say.

414
00:33:27,589 --> 00:33:30,672
Look, if I can make gods
out of rock-and-roll stars...

415
00:33:30,759 --> 00:33:32,750
imagine what I can do for you.

416
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:36,712
For your information,
I am not a rock-and-roll star.

417
00:33:36,806 --> 00:33:40,140
The people must believe
I have the same powers as the Jewel.

418
00:33:40,227 --> 00:33:42,343
Come. I want to see him now.

419
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:46,055
If it weren't for the Jewel,
I'd have led my people to power long ago.

420
00:33:56,159 --> 00:33:58,070
You Westerners understand nothing.

421
00:33:58,161 --> 00:34:01,279
The Jewel represents
the spiritual world of my people.

422
00:34:01,373 --> 00:34:03,956
Unless I can convince them
I am their spiritual leader...

423
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:05,953
they will never follow me
into battle.

424
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:08,581
That is why you are here.

425
00:34:32,696 --> 00:34:34,983
Tell me how it's done, magician.

426
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:37,531
It's not magic trick. It's miracle.

427
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:40,700
I am losing patience with you!

428
00:34:40,787 --> 00:34:44,997
But you cannot kill me.
Even you are superstitious.

429
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:48,166
- Al-Jawhara lives.
- Al-Jawhara?

430
00:34:48,253 --> 00:34:50,745
Two nights from now, it will not matter.

431
00:34:50,839 --> 00:34:52,830
Yallah!

432
00:35:06,229 --> 00:35:08,391
Oh, no.

433
00:35:12,319 --> 00:35:14,686
A woman?

434
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:16,611
Most unexpected.

435
00:35:16,698 --> 00:35:20,157
I gotta get outta here.
I gotta stop Omar.

436
00:35:20,243 --> 00:35:22,325
Did you bring an army?

437
00:35:22,412 --> 00:35:25,279
What? No. I'm ju-
I'm just Joan Wilder.

438
00:35:25,373 --> 00:35:27,489
Just-Joan Wilder,
I'm Al-Jawhara.

439
00:35:27,584 --> 00:35:29,746
Al-Jawhara?

440
00:35:29,836 --> 00:35:31,747
The Jewel of the Nile.

441
00:35:31,838 --> 00:35:36,378
I don't understand.
You're the Jewel?

442
00:35:36,468 --> 00:35:38,835
Eh, for the moment.

443
00:35:38,928 --> 00:35:41,386
In two nights,
at the holy city of Kadir...

444
00:35:41,473 --> 00:35:43,965
Omar will proclaim himself emperor.

445
00:35:44,059 --> 00:35:48,599
Without me to oppose him, he'll
march across North Africa like a madman.

446
00:35:48,688 --> 00:35:52,477
- But the world
will see me as the savior of my people.

447
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:54,899
No, it won't.
The world won't believe you.

448
00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:57,478
I've been in your office,
and I've seen your vision.

449
00:35:57,572 --> 00:35:59,904
- I'm gonna write the truth about you!
- The truth?

450
00:35:59,991 --> 00:36:03,234
If I wanted the truth,
I would have hired 60 Minutes.

451
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:06,411
What do you know about truth?
You fantasize everything.

452
00:36:06,498 --> 00:36:08,580
Why do you think
I brought you here?

453
00:36:08,667 --> 00:36:11,955
You stay here, and you write
what I tell you to write.

454
00:36:13,546 --> 00:36:15,537
You think no one knows I'm here?

455
00:36:15,632 --> 00:36:17,714
Oh, yes. Jack.
I forgot to tell you.

456
00:36:17,801 --> 00:36:19,667
Jack is dead.

457
00:36:21,513 --> 00:36:25,302
Don't be ridiculous.
Jack would never die without telling me.

458
00:36:25,392 --> 00:36:27,429
Nevertheless, he is dead.

459
00:36:34,567 --> 00:36:36,478
You look pale, Miss Wilder.

460
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:39,106
I'll send you my personal physician.

461
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:48,157
It can't be true.

462
00:36:53,670 --> 00:36:57,254
This Jack, he is friend for you?

463
00:36:58,717 --> 00:37:00,628
Yes.

464
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:02,630
He is my best friend.

465
00:37:14,983 --> 00:37:17,850
I- I don't see shit.

466
00:37:18,987 --> 00:37:20,898
We must stop here.

467
00:37:20,989 --> 00:37:23,902
It is dangerous for Sufis
to enter Omar's city.

468
00:37:23,992 --> 00:37:27,656
Now, wait a minute.
This guy's already tried to kill me once.

469
00:37:29,914 --> 00:37:32,656
You are guest of Omar.

470
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:35,960
Find for us the Jewel.
Accept your destiny.

471
00:37:37,464 --> 00:37:40,252
Destiny, my ass.

472
00:37:41,801 --> 00:37:44,463
When you hook up with a bunch of Jujubes,
you see what happens?

473
00:37:44,554 --> 00:37:47,888
Just take your lead from me,
and we'll be fine.

474
00:37:47,974 --> 00:37:50,966
What are we gonna do,
walk right through the center of town?

475
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:53,496
I'm gonna put you up a
camel's ass for openers.

476
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:54,849
I think I might like it.

477
00:37:57,442 --> 00:38:01,982
What are you doing?

478
00:38:02,071 --> 00:38:05,564
In one of my books-
Angelina's Savage Secret-

479
00:38:05,658 --> 00:38:09,993
she used her nail file to cut the mortar
away from the window bars.

480
00:38:10,079 --> 00:38:12,616
How long did this take?

481
00:38:12,707 --> 00:38:15,324
Two pages.

482
00:38:15,418 --> 00:38:19,457
Eh, but it's not the bars that
make the prison. It is the desert.

483
00:38:19,547 --> 00:38:22,835
So I'll travel at night.
I don't care. I have to stop Omar.

484
00:38:22,926 --> 00:38:26,214
I gotta get out of here
if I'm gonna write the truth about him.

485
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:28,887
I have to get to Kadir.

486
00:38:28,973 --> 00:38:32,386
Wait a minute.
You're the one that has to get to Kadir.

487
00:38:32,477 --> 00:38:35,765
You're the only one that can stop Omar.
You have to go with me.

488
00:38:35,855 --> 00:38:38,517
Ah. Hmm.

489
00:38:38,608 --> 00:38:40,770
Maybe you are the one.

490
00:38:42,445 --> 00:38:44,356
I accept.

491
00:38:44,447 --> 00:38:46,609
We are sworn, Just-Joan.

492
00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:52,195
- Right. But it's just Joan.
- Right. Just-Joan.

493
00:38:52,288 --> 00:38:54,575
Right. We just have
to get out this window.

494
00:38:54,666 --> 00:38:56,828
Please. Please.

495
00:38:57,836 --> 00:38:59,747
Please.

496
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:04,123
- Magic.
- Dry rot.

497
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:09,799
I bet you could pick up
a swell three-bedroom townhouse here...

498
00:39:09,889 --> 00:39:13,883
for about five or six dollars.

499
00:39:13,977 --> 00:39:15,934
Hiya, guys.

500
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:18,933
My name is Colton.
I've been invited by your Omar.

501
00:39:19,023 --> 00:39:21,014
I'm here to see Joan Wilder.

502
00:39:21,109 --> 00:39:23,601
Rachid!

503
00:39:23,695 --> 00:39:25,982
Hey, Rachid, how are you?
Good to see you again.

504
00:39:26,072 --> 00:39:28,359
Joan Wilder does not
want to see you.

505
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:35,533
Well, now, Rachid,
I don't think you understand.

506
00:39:36,958 --> 00:39:39,074
Uh, we're here on official business.

507
00:39:39,168 --> 00:39:42,627
Now, this is Mr., uh, Fatush
from the US. Embassy.

508
00:39:42,714 --> 00:39:45,376
He's got something very important
to talk to all you guys about.

509
00:39:49,429 --> 00:39:53,844
Yeah. Look, we don't want to create
an international incident here.

510
00:39:53,933 --> 00:39:57,051
After all, she is
an American citizen.

511
00:39:57,145 --> 00:39:59,637
If you'll just let us see her-
no paperwork.

512
00:39:59,731 --> 00:40:01,688
Mum's the word.
Everything will be-

513
00:40:03,776 --> 00:40:07,440
Guys, no sweat. We'll catch
you next time we're in town.

514
00:40:07,530 --> 00:40:09,817
- Take it easy.
- Say hello to her for us.

515
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:13,617
You know what they say-Once they've
had a holy man, they never go back.

516
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:15,614
Quickly, Just-Joan!

517
00:40:15,705 --> 00:40:18,037
Are you sure you know
where you're going?

518
00:40:23,588 --> 00:40:26,797
I heard those guys can go for hours
without comin' up for air.

519
00:40:26,883 --> 00:40:30,842
Ease up, will you? There's gotta be
another way in here some place.

520
00:40:30,929 --> 00:40:33,717
I can't wait for another smooth move
from Dr. Doom.

521
00:40:33,806 --> 00:40:36,514
How about you and me
at the back door in pussycat suits?

522
00:40:36,601 --> 00:40:38,683
When they come
with the saucer of milk-

523
00:40:38,770 --> 00:40:41,228
- How about you taking it in the ear?
- Ooh! Very-

524
00:40:41,314 --> 00:40:44,056
Look, pal, if it wasn't for me,
you wouldn't be onto this.

525
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:47,313
Subsequently, I should shoot you
the first chance I get.

526
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:50,145
Jack! You're alive!

527
00:40:50,239 --> 00:40:53,573
Kind of going outta
your way to duck me, aren't you?

528
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:56,072
- You bastard!
- Just-Joan!

529
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:07,579
Oh! Jack!
I thought I'd never see you again.

530
00:41:07,674 --> 00:41:09,961
They told me you were dead,
and I believed them!

531
00:41:10,051 --> 00:41:13,635
- I never wanna feel that way again!
- Does this mean you apologize?

532
00:41:13,721 --> 00:41:16,213
I feel like I'm back in eighth grade here.

533
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:18,264
What is this-
The Young and the Stupid?

534
00:41:18,351 --> 00:41:20,262
What the hell is he doing here?

535
00:41:20,353 --> 00:41:23,641
Don't get cagey with me, sweetheart.
I'm onto it.

536
00:41:23,731 --> 00:41:25,688
I know how you two operate.

537
00:41:28,111 --> 00:41:31,229
I'll get in there
with or without you dinks!

538
00:41:39,622 --> 00:41:42,535
Hey, look, guys.
Lighten up, will you?

539
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:45,037
I only said hello
to an old girlfriend here.

540
00:41:45,128 --> 00:41:47,039
Just-Joan! We need to go!

541
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:49,371
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
Who's this guy?

542
00:41:49,465 --> 00:41:51,456
- He's a friend.
- You made friends in there?

543
00:42:07,859 --> 00:42:11,648
- Okay, let's go. Come on.
- Wait, wait. He's coming with us.

544
00:42:11,738 --> 00:42:16,653
Don't start with me! All right? I've come
halfway across Africa to rescue you.

545
00:42:16,743 --> 00:42:19,485
Rescue me?
I was doin' fine without you!

546
00:42:19,579 --> 00:42:22,571
I am guide. I can help you.

547
00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:26,033
- I don't need a guide! I need a miracle!
- Jack, he's coming with us.

548
00:42:29,047 --> 00:42:33,587
All right! But if we get out of this alive,
I'm gonna kill you!

549
00:42:33,676 --> 00:42:35,713
Let's go. Come on.

550
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:52,393
Al-Jawhara!

551
00:43:11,297 --> 00:43:13,504
- Who are you?
- Is this where Al Jolson's buried?

552
00:43:13,591 --> 00:43:14,814
Who the hell are you?

553
00:43:14,838 --> 00:43:17,550
Hey! Don't provoke
me, pal' I had a tough day.

554
00:43:17,637 --> 00:43:21,847
You know how hot it is here?
It's 120 degrees in the shade.

555
00:43:21,933 --> 00:43:24,675
I'm like this with Weinberger.

556
00:43:24,769 --> 00:43:28,012
We'll be all over you like a cheap suit.

557
00:43:30,525 --> 00:43:34,564
Yallah!

558
00:43:34,654 --> 00:43:36,645
Let me in!
Let me in! Oh!

559
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:40,903
Holy shit!
And shove me in it!

560
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:15,187
Oh, no! Over the wall!

561
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:34,664
Uh!

562
00:44:34,755 --> 00:44:36,666
Ooh! Ooh!

563
00:44:48,686 --> 00:44:51,644
Oh! Excuse me. Excuse me.
Excuse me. Excuse me.

564
00:44:55,443 --> 00:44:59,107
Come on. Move it! Oy! Ow! Oh, no! No!

565
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:06,776
Okay, fly boy, your estimated
time of departure's right now!

566
00:45:25,181 --> 00:45:28,515
- What are you doing?
- I'm not doing anything!

567
00:45:28,601 --> 00:45:33,186
- Well, do something!
- All right! I'm trying!

568
00:45:36,108 --> 00:45:38,691
I mean, this isn't Space Invaders!

569
00:45:43,908 --> 00:45:46,366
Jack! The wall!

570
00:45:46,452 --> 00:45:48,534
Aw, no!

571
00:46:27,743 --> 00:46:29,859
It is Space Invaders.

572
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:32,286
Wahoo! That'll show 'em!

573
00:46:42,091 --> 00:46:43,957
All right! Yeah!

574
00:46:44,051 --> 00:46:50,634
Oh, shit Jack.
Let's get outta here.

575
00:47:06,866 --> 00:47:10,279
This is gonna be tight!

576
00:47:13,998 --> 00:47:16,615
This is my first time in airplane.

577
00:47:27,386 --> 00:47:30,504
- Oh. Uh-
- How do you stop this thing?

578
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:40,305
Sorry.

579
00:47:48,157 --> 00:47:50,945
- Do you know where you're going?
- Give me a break, will ya?

580
00:48:26,821 --> 00:48:28,232
Al-Jawhara!

581
00:48:35,663 --> 00:48:38,701
- Your friend steal the Jewel!
- What?

582
00:48:43,379 --> 00:48:46,417
- You-You are liar to me!
- No!

583
00:48:46,507 --> 00:48:49,875
I come back, and you are dead!

584
00:48:54,140 --> 00:48:57,349
Colton, you thieving bastard!
You ain't stiffin' me again!

585
00:48:57,435 --> 00:49:00,553
I promise you!
I'll feed you to the maggots!

586
00:49:00,646 --> 00:49:07,601
I'll... Al-Jawhara! - Al-Jawhara!

587
00:49:08,779 --> 00:49:11,487
Al-Jawhara!

588
00:50:00,456 --> 00:50:02,367
Oh, great!
We're out of quarters.

589
00:50:02,458 --> 00:50:04,495
Well-Try that one there.

590
00:50:08,881 --> 00:50:12,624
Now what? Damn it!

591
00:50:21,519 --> 00:50:24,762
Yes!

592
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:29,725
- Yes!
- Hey, that's not bad for your first time.

593
00:51:04,103 --> 00:51:06,265
Come on. We got 'im.
We got 'im.

594
00:51:06,355 --> 00:51:08,892
Colton, you ain't gettin' away.

595
00:51:11,777 --> 00:51:16,066
♪♪

596
00:51:29,670 --> 00:51:32,753
Where the hell's the horn?

597
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:35,923
Get outta here!
Get outta the way! Come on!

598
00:51:52,818 --> 00:51:55,560
Sandstorm!

599
00:52:05,289 --> 00:52:08,077
Stop! Stop! Stop!

600
00:52:08,167 --> 00:52:10,875
What are you gonna do?

601
00:52:10,961 --> 00:52:14,955
Either save us or kill us.
Hang on!

602
00:53:13,440 --> 00:53:16,603
No!

603
00:53:16,694 --> 00:53:19,152
- Now you are dead.
- Don't cut off my head! Please!

604
00:53:19,238 --> 00:53:21,730
- You stole our Jewel.
- No! It wasn't me! It was the mook!

605
00:53:21,824 --> 00:53:24,612
He's constantly screwing me!
I swear to God on my eyes!

606
00:53:24,702 --> 00:53:26,909
I never seen that jewel!

607
00:53:26,995 --> 00:53:28,906
No, wait! No, wait, wait!

608
00:53:28,997 --> 00:53:31,329
Wait! Wait! wait!
You need me.

609
00:53:31,417 --> 00:53:34,660
- I can help you find him.
- You are his friend.

610
00:53:34,753 --> 00:53:37,620
No! No, no! Friend?
Stop saying that.

611
00:53:37,715 --> 00:53:39,672
Friends don't stab
each other in the back.

612
00:53:39,758 --> 00:53:43,501
Come on, look.
Look, we-we'll team up.

613
00:53:43,595 --> 00:53:45,336
We'll find the mook,
get 'im good.

614
00:53:45,431 --> 00:53:47,468
He knows that I will not be denied.

615
00:53:47,558 --> 00:53:49,720
Colton's future is bleak.

616
00:53:49,810 --> 00:53:51,721
Very bleak!

617
00:53:55,232 --> 00:53:57,143
Any idea where we are?

618
00:53:57,234 --> 00:53:59,145
Well, the best
I can figure out...

619
00:53:59,236 --> 00:54:02,319
is, if we head due east,
we should make it to the border.

620
00:54:02,406 --> 00:54:05,148
But-Is that the way to Kadir?

621
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:07,904
Laa. Kadir is in the west,
over that mountain.

622
00:54:07,995 --> 00:54:11,613
The best of luck to you, pal.
Joan, come on. Let's get going.

623
00:54:11,707 --> 00:54:14,620
Jack, we have to take him to Kadir.

624
00:54:14,710 --> 00:54:17,122
What are you talking about?
We got him out like you said.

625
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:19,123
The guy's gonna be fine.
Now come on.

626
00:54:19,214 --> 00:54:22,582
We swore an oath, Just-Joan and I.
We go to Kadir.

627
00:54:22,676 --> 00:54:27,011
What is it with you? Geez!

628
00:54:27,097 --> 00:54:29,338
I mean, everything's always
got to be your way?

629
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:32,391
- This is just like the goddamn boat!
- What do you mean, my way?

630
00:54:32,478 --> 00:54:35,266
It wasn't my idea
to spend six months on your boat!

631
00:54:35,355 --> 00:54:39,770
- Oh! Debate good. I enjoy.
- Let me tell you what I put up with.

632
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:42,693
We're moored
off the Canary Islands, right?

633
00:54:42,780 --> 00:54:46,865
Midnight-sound asleep-
three crazed Joan Wilder fans...

634
00:54:46,950 --> 00:54:50,614
decide they want the anchor
of the Angelina for a souvenir!

635
00:54:50,704 --> 00:54:53,822
- We were drifting for days! And what
about the other time... Stop. I'm sorry.

636
00:54:53,916 --> 00:54:56,203
It's time for Just-Joan.

637
00:54:56,293 --> 00:54:59,331
- Remember the Costa Del Sol, Jack?
- Aw, come on.

638
00:54:59,421 --> 00:55:02,288
He's got to meet me at the governor's
for a formal dinner.

639
00:55:02,382 --> 00:55:07,377
And you show up with the entire
Italian national basketball team!

640
00:55:07,471 --> 00:55:11,055
- Hey, they were hungry.
- This is exactly what I'm talking about.

641
00:55:11,141 --> 00:55:13,052
I just wish sometimes
you could think about me.

642
00:55:13,143 --> 00:55:17,182
Oh! Oh, and I suppose you were thinking all
about me when you took off with Omar, huh?

643
00:55:17,272 --> 00:55:19,559
- Did I tell you he blew up my boat?
- Our boat.

644
00:55:19,650 --> 00:55:21,857
- Oh. Now it's our boat.
- Is good. Good debate.

645
00:55:21,944 --> 00:55:24,982
Is equal. No winners.
Just-Joan, we must hurry.

646
00:55:25,072 --> 00:55:27,313
No, wait. What do you mean
he blew up our boat?

647
00:55:27,407 --> 00:55:30,274
Just tell me one thing.
Why are you risking your life for this guy?

648
00:55:30,369 --> 00:55:34,363
I made a commitment.
I can't break it.

649
00:55:37,334 --> 00:55:39,701
Okay.

650
00:55:39,795 --> 00:55:41,911
Okay, fine.

651
00:55:42,005 --> 00:55:44,838
I'm gonna tell you the truth.
I didn't come here for you anyway.

652
00:55:44,925 --> 00:55:48,008
No. I'm onto something big.

653
00:55:49,638 --> 00:55:51,675
A jewel-the Jewel of the Nile.

654
00:55:51,765 --> 00:55:54,723
Come with us.
I am Jawhara.

655
00:55:54,810 --> 00:55:56,926
Uh, that means “Joe.”

656
00:55:57,020 --> 00:55:59,227
Thanks, Joe, but no thanks.

657
00:55:59,314 --> 00:56:01,476
I wouldn't want her
to break her commitment.

658
00:56:02,484 --> 00:56:04,395
Aw, Jack.

659
00:56:04,486 --> 00:56:06,944
I mean, come on.

660
00:56:45,694 --> 00:56:47,605
That's for the Angelina.

661
00:56:49,239 --> 00:56:51,276
I still owe you for Joan.

662
00:56:54,828 --> 00:56:56,819
Oh, no. Oh, God.

663
00:56:56,914 --> 00:56:59,656
Please, let me get outta this alive.

664
00:56:59,750 --> 00:57:03,334
I swear to God.
I'll be a good boy from tomorrow on.

665
00:57:03,420 --> 00:57:08,290
Al-Jawhara!

666
00:57:08,383 --> 00:57:11,250
But, tonight, I gotta kill Colton.

667
00:57:24,566 --> 00:57:27,479
Joan Wilder!

668
00:57:28,570 --> 00:57:31,653
Val/ah! Val/ah!

669
00:57:41,249 --> 00:57:43,832
Why you didn't want
to tell your friend about me?

670
00:57:43,919 --> 00:57:45,830
Oh, I know him.

671
00:57:45,921 --> 00:57:47,941
He'd go halfway around the world
for a great party...

672
00:57:47,965 --> 00:57:50,423
but he wouldn't go across town
for a noble cause.

673
00:57:50,509 --> 00:57:54,343
- People can surprise you.
- No. He's just Jack. He'll never change.

674
00:57:54,429 --> 00:57:58,172
Like, uh-Like a stone.

675
00:57:58,266 --> 00:58:00,553
It's always a stone.

676
00:58:00,644 --> 00:58:02,601
Open your hand.

677
00:58:03,981 --> 00:58:07,645
Change is not always visible.

678
00:58:07,734 --> 00:58:10,021
All right!
Let's show some hustle!

679
00:58:10,112 --> 00:58:12,023
- What?
- Your buddy, Omar!

680
00:58:12,114 --> 00:58:15,698
What is it?
He can't live without you?

681
00:58:18,954 --> 00:58:21,696
- Are we jogging?
- We are jogging!

682
00:58:34,511 --> 00:58:36,843
Greece is looking better and better.

683
00:58:36,930 --> 00:58:38,841
Uh-huh.

684
00:58:45,355 --> 00:58:47,346
Aw, shit.

685
00:58:49,317 --> 00:58:53,276
Will you just tell me why the hell
this guy wants you so bad?

686
00:58:53,363 --> 00:58:55,274
- Hey, Joe, where you goin'?
- Uh, this way.

687
00:58:55,365 --> 00:58:57,276
You gotta be kidding.

688
00:58:57,367 --> 00:58:59,345
He probably knows the mountains
better than you, Jack.

689
00:58:59,369 --> 00:59:01,781
Joan, will you give me a break?
Will ya?

690
00:59:01,872 --> 00:59:05,490
America-democracy.
We vote, huh?

691
00:59:57,260 --> 01:00:00,594
Stop! Stop!

692
01:00:05,852 --> 01:00:07,934
It's him!

693
01:00:11,608 --> 01:00:14,817
Hurry up! Let's go! Let's go!

694
01:00:14,903 --> 01:00:16,814
Come on!
Get down! Get down!

695
01:00:20,992 --> 01:00:25,202
- It's a black day for democracy.
- Do not worry.

696
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:27,620
I'm sure it's not my destiny
to die on this mountain.

697
01:00:27,707 --> 01:00:31,245
- What about us?
- That's another ball game.

698
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:42,339
Rachid!

699
01:00:47,602 --> 01:00:52,267
Joan Wilder,
I wish no harm to you.

700
01:00:52,357 --> 01:00:55,270
I'm your friend, your fan.

701
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:57,897
Please surrender.

702
01:00:57,988 --> 01:01:01,276
What'd you do for this guy Omar
you never did for me?

703
01:01:01,366 --> 01:01:03,482
Bloody bitch.

704
01:01:14,212 --> 01:01:16,169
Oh, shit! Look out!

705
01:01:49,080 --> 01:01:52,072
Hey, Omar!
Eat rock shit!

706
01:01:52,167 --> 01:01:54,033
Let's go over there.

707
01:02:22,739 --> 01:02:25,197
I got something.

708
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:30,368
Nubians.

709
01:02:30,455 --> 01:02:33,573
I was hoping to avoid them.

710
01:02:40,257 --> 01:02:42,419
Sell any books here?

711
01:02:45,845 --> 01:02:47,756
Main man. Hey! My man!

712
01:02:47,847 --> 01:02:51,010
- What are you so happy about?
- Just keep smiling.

713
01:02:51,101 --> 01:02:54,093
Maybe they'll think
we're from National Geographic.

714
01:03:00,318 --> 01:03:02,605
Hey, how you doing, you guys?

715
01:03:04,447 --> 01:03:06,404
How you doing?

716
01:03:32,684 --> 01:03:36,518
He says it's many days long trip
over high mountains.

717
01:03:36,604 --> 01:03:38,515
And he wishes us
a very pleasant journey.

718
01:03:41,234 --> 01:03:42,092
Thank you. Thank you.

719
01:03:42,116 --> 01:03:43,879
Thank you. Thank you.
Thank you very much.

720
01:03:43,903 --> 01:03:45,965
- You're all right. Thank you, guys.
- Thank you. Excuse us.

721
01:03:45,989 --> 01:03:48,071
Catch you next time, all right?
Good-bye.

722
01:03:48,158 --> 01:03:50,946
Come on, Jack.

723
01:03:52,954 --> 01:03:56,072
Ah, Mr. Jack, Just-Joan.
The chief's son-

724
01:03:56,166 --> 01:03:59,124
He wishes to make a blessing
for your marriage and your children.

725
01:03:59,210 --> 01:04:03,704
We're not married.

726
01:04:24,402 --> 01:04:26,689
He says,
because you are not married...

727
01:04:26,780 --> 01:04:29,647
that, uh, his son
wishes to court you.

728
01:04:29,741 --> 01:04:33,450
- I just-
- No, that's, uh-

729
01:04:33,536 --> 01:04:37,905
That's very nice, but the lady is, uh-
She's with me.

730
01:04:43,505 --> 01:04:46,793
He says that because
there is more than one suitor...

731
01:04:46,883 --> 01:04:49,420
that you must wrestle his son.

732
01:04:49,511 --> 01:04:51,422
I gotta wrestle his son?

733
01:04:52,847 --> 01:04:56,511
Uh-huh.

734
01:04:56,601 --> 01:04:58,558
How you doing?

735
01:05:02,107 --> 01:05:05,145
Okay. This one,
I think I can handle.

736
01:05:05,235 --> 01:05:07,146
Okay.

737
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:13,360
No?

738
01:05:13,451 --> 01:05:16,443
Hyacinthe!

739
01:05:16,538 --> 01:05:18,870
Hyacinthe!

740
01:05:33,721 --> 01:05:36,554
Hey, but, guys, this is cuckoo
Wait a minute, guys.

741
01:05:36,641 --> 01:05:39,759
Let's talk this over like gentlemen,
all right? Come on!

742
01:05:42,188 --> 01:05:46,648
All right! You guys are for me, huh?
Yeah, me. All right.

743
01:05:46,734 --> 01:05:50,602
Do me a favor. Tell him we lived together
for six months. Aw, shit.

744
01:05:50,697 --> 01:05:53,314
All right. All right.
What are the rules?

745
01:06:17,015 --> 01:06:18,972
- Right.
- Yeah!

746
01:06:29,861 --> 01:06:33,604
- Oh! Oh!
- I'm really sorry about that.

747
01:06:34,949 --> 01:06:37,532
Oh, no! Not the left one!

748
01:06:40,413 --> 01:06:44,247
- Jack!
- No pain, no gain.

749
01:06:44,334 --> 01:06:46,325
Oh, let me go!

750
01:06:51,966 --> 01:06:55,084
No! No!

751
01:06:55,178 --> 01:06:58,011
- Can we talk about this?
- Stop it!

752
01:06:59,807 --> 01:07:02,265
We have to do something!

753
01:07:02,352 --> 01:07:04,593
I am doing something.

754
01:07:09,817 --> 01:07:12,058
Oh!

755
01:07:25,959 --> 01:07:28,917
Joe, he's-

756
01:07:35,510 --> 01:07:38,719
No!

757
01:07:38,805 --> 01:07:41,217
Ay!

758
01:08:20,305 --> 01:08:25,550
Yeah!

759
01:08:25,643 --> 01:08:27,680
Yea!

760
01:08:27,770 --> 01:08:29,886
Aha! Yeah!

761
01:08:30,940 --> 01:08:32,897
That was great!

762
01:08:32,984 --> 01:08:35,897
Great, huh?
I could have gotten killed!

763
01:08:35,987 --> 01:08:38,695
♪♪

764
01:08:38,781 --> 01:08:41,739
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

765
01:09:32,126 --> 01:09:34,163
This is the marriage dance.

766
01:09:34,253 --> 01:09:36,995
In this tribe, the women-
They choose the men.

767
01:09:37,090 --> 01:09:39,206
And then according
to the custom...

768
01:09:39,300 --> 01:09:41,260
they will be together
for the rest of their lives.

769
01:09:41,302 --> 01:09:44,010
- They get all that from one dance?
- Eh-heh.

770
01:09:44,097 --> 01:09:46,008
I think it's beautiful.

771
01:09:50,853 --> 01:09:53,390
Ralph, if you want to be one of us...

772
01:09:53,481 --> 01:09:55,472
take off your shoes and socks.

773
01:09:57,110 --> 01:10:00,853
If you want to be one of us, you must see
with the eyes of your heart...

774
01:10:00,947 --> 01:10:03,655
- not with the eyes of your head.
- Gotcha, yeah.

775
01:10:03,741 --> 01:10:06,233
Your heart will never
give you fear or pain...

776
01:10:06,327 --> 01:10:09,035
if you know our way.

777
01:10:11,582 --> 01:10:14,791
- Ralph.
- Uh, no, thanks, pal.

778
01:10:14,877 --> 01:10:18,666
- Keep your friggin' jewel. No! Hey! Hey!
- Are you afraid?

779
01:10:18,756 --> 01:10:21,464
Well, I just had my feet resoled.

780
01:10:21,551 --> 01:10:23,758
What is the worst
that can happen to you?

781
01:10:23,845 --> 01:10:25,961
I could wind up
a Chicken McNugget.

782
01:10:26,055 --> 01:10:28,638
What is the best
that could happen to you?

783
01:10:28,725 --> 01:10:31,717
I could get through this
and find the jewel.

784
01:10:31,811 --> 01:10:35,304
It's your choice. Look down.

785
01:10:40,194 --> 01:10:43,437
Hot coals! Hot coals!

786
01:10:45,408 --> 01:10:47,649
I did it! I did it!
I'm one of us!

787
01:10:47,744 --> 01:10:49,906
Ya ya ya ya!

788
01:10:50,037 --> 01:10:54,201
♪♪

789
01:11:15,021 --> 01:11:17,262
All right! Yeah!

790
01:11:31,579 --> 01:11:33,786
Yeah!

791
01:11:42,924 --> 01:11:46,667
Your fears-
They make you foolish.

792
01:11:52,058 --> 01:11:53,969
Go to her, Jack.

793
01:13:16,058 --> 01:13:19,517
I'm sorry I got people
shooting at you again, Jack.

794
01:13:19,604 --> 01:13:23,939
Are you kidding? We're the perfect couple
when we got people shootin' at us.

795
01:13:24,025 --> 01:13:26,187
It's just the slow times
I'm not too good at.

796
01:13:26,277 --> 01:13:27,984
I guess I just expect too much.

797
01:13:28,070 --> 01:13:30,903
Maybe we both expect too much.

798
01:13:33,868 --> 01:13:36,075
Oh, boy.

799
01:13:37,830 --> 01:13:40,413
Thank you for coming
to Kadir with me.

800
01:14:08,402 --> 01:14:11,110
This valley is gift of the Nile.

801
01:14:18,913 --> 01:14:21,951
I've been away
from here too long.

802
01:14:26,003 --> 01:14:29,291
I'm getting to like this guy Joe.
He's growing on me.

803
01:14:29,382 --> 01:14:31,999
What do you say we cut him in
on this jewel if we ever find it?

804
01:14:32,093 --> 01:14:37,762
Jack, uh... we have the Jewel.

805
01:14:38,975 --> 01:14:41,262
What are you talking about?
Where?

806
01:14:41,352 --> 01:14:44,140
Well, there.

807
01:14:46,607 --> 01:14:48,439
What, Joe's got the jewel?

808
01:14:48,526 --> 01:14:52,986
No. Joe is the Jewel.

809
01:14:56,826 --> 01:14:58,737
Joe is the Jewel of the Nile?

810
01:14:58,828 --> 01:15:03,618
He's a-a holy man.
That's his religious title.

811
01:15:05,459 --> 01:15:07,370
Joe's the Jewel.

812
01:15:15,678 --> 01:15:18,420
Why didn't you tell me the truth?
Why'd you keep it from me?

813
01:15:19,849 --> 01:15:22,716
Because I thought, if you knew,
you wouldn't come with us.

814
01:15:22,810 --> 01:15:25,723
Maybe I would've surprised you.

815
01:15:25,813 --> 01:15:28,601
I think I've come through once or twice,
if I remember right.

816
01:15:31,277 --> 01:15:33,735
I'm sorry. You're right.

817
01:15:33,821 --> 01:15:36,028
You come through all the time.

818
01:15:43,289 --> 01:15:45,951
It's funny.

819
01:15:46,042 --> 01:15:47,953
I really thought we had a chance.

820
01:16:02,558 --> 01:16:05,846
Ah! Look, Just-Joan-
the train to Kadir.

821
01:16:05,936 --> 01:16:09,179
Come on, Jack.
Inshallah, we'll be there tonight.

822
01:16:09,273 --> 01:16:12,061
- What a lot of people!
- Yes, those are pilgrims.

823
01:16:12,151 --> 01:16:14,859
- They are going to see the false redeemer.
- Omar again, huh?

824
01:16:14,945 --> 01:16:16,982
Well, we'll see about that.

825
01:16:52,399 --> 01:16:54,310
Oh, shit.

826
01:17:29,562 --> 01:17:31,473
Val/ah! Val/ah!

827
01:18:04,680 --> 01:18:07,012
What are you doing?

828
01:18:07,099 --> 01:18:09,761
Come on.

829
01:18:09,852 --> 01:18:11,684
Jump!

830
01:18:12,938 --> 01:18:16,772
No!

831
01:18:16,859 --> 01:18:19,851
- Jack!
- Hey.

832
01:18:21,697 --> 01:18:24,564
Jack!

833
01:18:46,847 --> 01:18:49,088
Hang on! Hang on, Joan!

834
01:19:08,369 --> 01:19:12,283
Jack, watch out!
It's-Aah!

835
01:19:28,389 --> 01:19:32,007
Al-Jawhara.

836
01:19:32,101 --> 01:19:35,014
Al-Jawhara!
Al-Jawhara!

837
01:19:37,273 --> 01:19:40,686
“Olly!” What?
Olly! Olly! Olly! Olly!

838
01:19:40,776 --> 01:19:44,565
Guys, wait up! Come on, Humphrey.
Go! Go! Go! Olly! Olly!

839
01:19:53,664 --> 01:19:56,281
Do something!

840
01:19:56,375 --> 01:19:58,332
What do you want me to do?

841
01:20:16,478 --> 01:20:20,267
Joan Wilder!

842
01:20:50,304 --> 01:20:53,513
SN

843
01:21:29,093 --> 01:21:31,835
Colton!

844
01:21:31,929 --> 01:21:34,170
Hah!

845
01:21:34,264 --> 01:21:37,802
Your ass is grass,
and I'm a lawn mower, Colton!

846
01:21:37,893 --> 01:21:40,726
Colton! I'll get you, Colton!
I'm onto you!

847
01:21:55,619 --> 01:21:59,362
Colton!

848
01:22:13,846 --> 01:22:15,803
Colton.

849
01:23:09,610 --> 01:23:12,398
Yea! All right! Yeah!

850
01:23:15,365 --> 01:23:18,574
All right, let's go.
Come on. Let's get outta here.

851
01:23:25,292 --> 01:23:31,416
Just-Joan, you're great-
Welcome, welcome.

852
01:23:31,507 --> 01:23:33,544
I don't usually travel by train...

853
01:23:33,634 --> 01:23:36,968
but I had a small accident
with my helicopter.

854
01:23:50,067 --> 01:23:54,026
May we reach Kadir in time.
Inshallah.

855
01:24:15,217 --> 01:24:18,426
Once we get inside,
we must find the entrance to the catacombs,

856
01:24:18,512 --> 01:24:22,301
Take home a T-shirt!
T-shirts! Buy T-shirts.

857
01:24:22,391 --> 01:24:24,382
Get outta here.
Give me the T-shirt.

858
01:24:24,476 --> 01:24:26,467
I'll buy it. I'll buy it.
Get outta here, will ya?

859
01:24:46,999 --> 01:24:51,414
You know,
I really admire your loyalty to each other.

860
01:24:51,503 --> 01:24:55,622
And I'm going to give you a chance
to be together to the very end.

861
01:24:55,716 --> 01:25:00,677
Well, not exactly. One
will watch the other die.

862
01:25:06,059 --> 01:25:08,801
But which one?

863
01:25:09,896 --> 01:25:12,479
Rachid.

864
01:25:12,566 --> 01:25:14,773
Is that the goat blood?

865
01:25:14,860 --> 01:25:16,771
Yes.

866
01:25:16,862 --> 01:25:20,981
Very popular with the inhabitants
of these catacombs,

867
01:25:21,074 --> 01:25:23,361
- Rats.
- Yes. And they will eat...

868
01:25:23,452 --> 01:25:25,693
until they get the very last drop.

869
01:25:25,787 --> 01:25:27,698
But don't worry, Mr. Colton.

870
01:25:27,789 --> 01:25:29,871
You won't be alone.

871
01:25:29,958 --> 01:25:32,495
Rachid is now placing acid..

872
01:25:32,586 --> 01:25:35,044
That will eat through
Miss Wilder's rope.

873
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:39,715
What kind of sick pervert would go
to this trouble? Why don't you shoot us?

874
01:25:39,801 --> 01:25:40,548
Jack!

875
01:25:40,572 --> 01:25:42,884
I mean, what kind of
demented psychopath...

876
01:25:42,971 --> 01:25:46,214
- would even think of this?
- The Savage Secret.

877
01:25:46,308 --> 01:25:50,472
- What?
- It was my biggest seller.

878
01:25:50,562 --> 01:25:53,475
Oh.

879
01:25:53,565 --> 01:25:59,151
Think about this pit
as your last adventure, Joan Wilder.

880
01:26:00,364 --> 01:26:03,982
My people await me. Rachid!

881
01:26:23,178 --> 01:26:26,421
What you talkin' about? I'm used
to workin' with professional people.

882
01:26:26,515 --> 01:26:30,725
You tell His Highness
the show starts with him or without him.

883
01:26:38,193 --> 01:26:42,278
Goddamn beanie convention.
We'll end up going home with a rug.

884
01:26:42,364 --> 01:26:44,446
The entrance.

885
01:26:55,961 --> 01:26:58,123
Give me a red
to the yellow and cue!

886
01:26:58,213 --> 01:27:00,124
♪♪

887
01:27:00,215 --> 01:27:02,673
I said give me
a red gel down there!

888
01:27:08,557 --> 01:27:11,549
And cue!
For God's sake, cue!

889
01:27:15,397 --> 01:27:19,356
♪♪

890
01:27:36,042 --> 01:27:39,205
Build it. Build it softly. Build it-
And give me some smoke.

891
01:28:09,493 --> 01:28:11,951
That's good. That's good.
That's very good. Now bring it up.

892
01:28:12,037 --> 01:28:14,950
Bring it up slowly.

893
01:28:36,728 --> 01:28:41,222
Omar! Omar!

894
01:28:41,316 --> 01:28:44,274
Omar! Omar!

895
01:28:44,361 --> 01:28:48,150
Omar! Omar!

896
01:28:48,240 --> 01:28:51,608
Omar! Omar!

897
01:29:10,637 --> 01:29:13,174
♪♪

898
01:29:29,239 --> 01:29:33,574
- Hey, hey, hey!
- There are many rooms and many ways.

899
01:29:33,660 --> 01:29:38,200
You, you go this way.
And you, you go this way.

900
01:29:38,290 --> 01:29:40,827
And we, we go this way.

901
01:29:59,728 --> 01:30:03,892
Oh, ooh! What a stench in this place.

902
01:30:08,236 --> 01:30:12,275
- What looks good, amigo?
- Uh, you go from this way.

903
01:30:12,365 --> 01:30:14,823
And, uh, I go this way.

904
01:30:14,910 --> 01:30:16,821
All right.

905
01:30:17,913 --> 01:30:19,950
Froot Loop.

906
01:30:21,625 --> 01:30:23,536
- So how'd they get out?
- What?

907
01:30:23,627 --> 01:30:25,584
In The Savage Secret,
how'd they get out?

908
01:30:25,670 --> 01:30:28,082
Oh. Uh...

909
01:30:28,173 --> 01:30:31,382
Jessie had a knife
hidden in his boot.

910
01:30:32,636 --> 01:30:34,718
You wouldn't happen
to have a knife, would you?

911
01:30:34,804 --> 01:30:37,341
I'm not even wearing underwear.

912
01:30:37,432 --> 01:30:39,343
Great.

913
01:30:39,434 --> 01:30:41,926
- Aah! Jack!
- No! No!

914
01:31:00,372 --> 01:31:02,955
We were good together,
weren't we, Joan Wilder?

915
01:31:03,041 --> 01:31:05,999
The best.

916
01:31:06,086 --> 01:31:09,169
- And we're gonna make it.
- Yeah.

917
01:31:12,425 --> 01:31:14,837
Oh, God, I love you, lady.

918
01:31:14,928 --> 01:31:16,919
I love you, Jack.

919
01:31:17,013 --> 01:31:21,598
- Will you marry me?
- Yes!

920
01:31:21,685 --> 01:31:23,926
Because I don't ever want you
leaving me again.

921
01:31:24,020 --> 01:31:28,639
You're not just saying that
because this is it, are you?

922
01:31:30,443 --> 01:31:34,437
I'm saying it because
I'm not afraid to say it anymore.

923
01:31:48,837 --> 01:31:50,748
So where you wanna go
on our honeymoon?

924
01:32:01,224 --> 01:32:05,889
Omar! Omar!

925
01:32:05,979 --> 01:32:08,812
Omar! Omar!

926
01:32:13,361 --> 01:32:17,605
Rats! Get out of here.
It's a goddamn rat farm. Go on!

927
01:32:17,699 --> 01:32:19,986
Ralph! Ralph,
get us out of here, will ya?

928
01:32:20,076 --> 01:32:23,444
Oh! And there's
the biggest rat of all.

929
01:32:23,538 --> 01:32:27,532
Ooh, Colton, look at you, you-

930
01:32:27,625 --> 01:32:30,242
You don't know how many nights
I dreamed of this very thing...

931
01:32:30,336 --> 01:32:34,830
- except your flesh was torn off your body.
- Please, just help us down.

932
01:32:34,924 --> 01:32:36,881
Jack, the rope!

933
01:32:39,179 --> 01:32:41,796
Well, well, well, Colton.

934
01:32:41,890 --> 01:32:46,475
I think this calls for a renegotiation.
Don't you, Tarzan? Huh?

935
01:32:46,561 --> 01:32:51,772
This looks a little bit more like 70-30
or maybe even 80-20.

936
01:32:51,858 --> 01:32:54,475
Ralph, will you get the rats off my rope!

937
01:32:54,569 --> 01:32:56,810
I don't go near rats, buddy.

938
01:32:56,905 --> 01:33:00,819
Ralph, do not be afraid.

939
01:33:00,909 --> 01:33:03,571
Remember the Sufi way.
See with your heart.

940
01:33:03,661 --> 01:33:07,871
My heart sees rats, pop.
Don't let this garb fool you.

941
01:33:07,957 --> 01:33:10,164
Come on, Colton,
where's the jewel?

942
01:33:10,251 --> 01:33:14,620
Ralph, I am the Jewel-
the Jewel of the Nile.

943
01:33:14,714 --> 01:33:16,671
Yeah, and I'm a kumquat
from Queens.

944
01:33:16,758 --> 01:33:19,295
- Pipe down, towel head!
- Come on, Ralph!

945
01:33:19,385 --> 01:33:21,251
Take the ladder
and put it over the well.

946
01:33:21,346 --> 01:33:24,964
- Please, please, don't let us die.
- That's a good idea, legs.

947
01:33:25,058 --> 01:33:27,925
I ain't gonna let you die,
but I ain't movin' no damn ladder...

948
01:33:28,019 --> 01:33:30,306
until you two
come across with the rock.

949
01:33:44,285 --> 01:33:47,698
Lookin' more like 90-10,
huh, kumquat?

950
01:33:47,789 --> 01:33:50,201
Uh, did you get the ladder
all right, buddy?

951
01:33:50,291 --> 01:33:53,579
- Jack, help me unlock the Jewel.
- The Jewel?

952
01:33:53,670 --> 01:33:57,208
You mean you weren't shittin' me?
That guy really is the Jewel?

953
01:33:57,298 --> 01:34:00,256
Come on. We still got time
to stop Omar! Let's go.

954
01:34:01,469 --> 01:34:04,587
Ralph, that is not the Sufi way.

955
01:34:04,681 --> 01:34:06,592
I don't know
what got into me, Jewels.

956
01:34:06,683 --> 01:34:09,550
Every time I'm around this guy,
he makes me crazy.

957
01:34:09,644 --> 01:34:12,011
Aw, come on.
Tell him to cut me down, Jewels.

958
01:34:12,105 --> 01:34:14,267
Come on. Come on, huh?

959
01:34:14,399 --> 01:34:18,688
Omar! Omar!

960
01:34:18,778 --> 01:34:22,772
Omar! Omar!

961
01:34:53,855 --> 01:34:55,516
Joan Wilder!

962
01:34:58,985 --> 01:35:03,070
Don't fuck around with the equipment!
Bloody woman!

963
01:35:06,034 --> 01:35:10,198
Joan Wilder!

964
01:35:24,636 --> 01:35:28,004
- Get them! Go!
- Here they come, Jack.

965
01:35:51,037 --> 01:35:52,948
Oh, my God. Look at this.

966
01:35:53,039 --> 01:35:55,121
Looks like Our Lady of Mount Carmel
school yard.

967
01:35:55,208 --> 01:35:58,542
H-Hold it!

968
01:36:03,925 --> 01:36:06,508
Excuse me. Pardon me.
Pardon me. Comin' through.

969
01:36:06,594 --> 01:36:11,088
Ho, ho, ho. Oh, Rachid.
How you doin'?

970
01:36:11,182 --> 01:36:13,970
Let's talk this over
before you butcher me alive.

971
01:36:14,060 --> 01:36:17,553
What are you gettin'
so steamed about?

972
01:36:17,647 --> 01:36:21,936
Look at that. It worked.

973
01:37:24,589 --> 01:37:26,705
Jawhara!

974
01:37:35,850 --> 01:37:37,286
Al-Jawhara!

975
01:37:37,310 --> 01:37:40,177
Al-Jawhara!

976
01:38:02,210 --> 01:38:04,451
Get over the wall!
Go on! Come on!

977
01:38:04,545 --> 01:38:07,537
Get going! Get going!

978
01:38:11,803 --> 01:38:13,714
Keep going!

979
01:38:38,996 --> 01:38:41,454
I knew we'd hook up again, Colton!

980
01:38:41,541 --> 01:38:43,578
Get it!

981
01:38:46,003 --> 01:38:50,918
I swear to God!
My right hand to God! Come on!

982
01:39:33,384 --> 01:39:35,500
I am dead, Miss Wilder.

983
01:39:35,595 --> 01:39:38,553
All that will be written for Omar
is an epitaph.

984
01:39:38,639 --> 01:39:42,428
But I will not be alone.

985
01:39:50,193 --> 01:39:53,276
Who is going
to save you now, hmm?

986
01:39:55,865 --> 01:39:57,447
Who?

987
01:40:38,366 --> 01:40:41,324
Well, you got your story.

988
01:40:41,410 --> 01:40:44,198
I got a lot more than that.

989
01:41:07,520 --> 01:41:09,477
You are married.

990
01:41:26,247 --> 01:41:29,615
♪♪

991
01:41:39,302 --> 01:41:42,010
Always a bridesmaid,
never the bride.

992
01:41:42,096 --> 01:41:44,884
As usual,
it's zilch for poor Ralphie.

993
01:41:47,518 --> 01:41:49,759
You are Sufi.

994
01:41:51,856 --> 01:41:54,223
Keep it always.

995
01:41:54,317 --> 01:41:56,809
Aw, guys!

996
01:41:56,902 --> 01:41:59,644
Ahh.

997
01:41:59,739 --> 01:42:01,821
Sufis rule!

998
01:42:01,907 --> 01:42:05,445
♪♪

999
01:42:08,873 --> 01:42:12,116
♪♪

1000
01:45:47,842 --> 01:45:51,005
♪♪